article.story: AMHERST, Mass. -- — Erik Reynolds II scored 31 points, Lynn Greer III made a putback with 1.4 seconds left and Saint Joseph's (Pa.) rallied from a 13-point deficit to take down UMass 78-77 on Tuesday night. Reynolds added three steals for the Hawks (13-6, 3-3 Atlantic 10 Conference). Xzayvier Brown scored 11 points while going 4 of 9 from the floor, including 1 for 4 from 3-point range, and 2 for 4 from the line. Rasheer Fleming went 3 of 8 from the field to finish with eight points. Rahsool Diggins led the Minutemen (12-7, 3-4) in scoring, finishing with 17 points and three steals. UMass also got 16 points, six rebounds and two blocks from Daniel Hankins-Sanford. Matt Cross also recorded 12 points, nine rebounds and four assists. Reynolds led Saint Joseph's with 13 points in the second half. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
